ENTRY       EC 2.8.3.22                 Enzyme
NAME        succinyl-CoA---L-malate CoA-transferase;
            SmtAB
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring sulfur-containing groups;
            CoA-transferases
SYSNAME     succinyl-CoA:(S)-malate CoA-transferase
REACTION    (1) succinyl-CoA + (S)-malate = succinate + (S)-malyl-CoA [RN:R00406];
            (2) succinyl-CoA + (S)-citramalate = succinate + (S)-citramalyl-CoA [RN:R03154]
ALL_REAC    R00406 R03154
SUBSTRATE   succinyl-CoA [CPD:C00091];
            (S)-malate [CPD:C00149];
            (S)-citramalate [CPD:C02614]
PRODUCT     succinate [CPD:C00042];
            (S)-malyl-CoA [CPD:C04348];
            (S)-citramalyl-CoA [CPD:C01011]
COMMENT     The enzyme, purified from the bacterium Chloroflexus aurantiacus, can also accept itaconate as acceptor, with lower efficiency. It is part of the 3-hydroxypropanoate cycle for carbon assimilation.
